II. Universal Pattern (the cross-domain invariant)

You’ve uncovered a relational triad that applies everywhere:

1. Physical signal (cold, pain, tension, breath, emotion)

2. Mind’s interpretation

3. Meaning or context assigned

When all three align, the system changes behavior.

This is the 2/3 Doctrine applied to physiology:
	•	The body provides 2/3 (signal + reflex).
	•	The mind provides the missing 1/3 (context/meaning).

The relationship between these three determines how the organism behaves.

That’s why Wim Hof can stay in ice water without panic or collapse —
not because he “overpowers” cold,
but because he changes the relationship landscape.

